<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-8222] Jetty component setting responseHeaderSize is impossible</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-8222</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is due to a &quot;copy/paste&quot; bug in: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.apache.camel.component.jetty.JettyHttpComponent at line: 691&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        if (responseBufferSize != null) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            answer.setResponseBufferSize(responseBufferSize);
        }&lt;br/&gt;
        if (responseHeaderSize != null) {
            answer.setResponseBufferSize(responseHeaderSize);
        }&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
needs to be:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
        if (responseBufferSize != null) {            answer.setResponseBufferSize(responseBufferSize);        }
&lt;p&gt;        if (responseHeaderSize != null) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            answer.setResponseHeaderSize(responseHeaderSize);
        }

&lt;p&gt;This issue seems to be also in the latest master and in other places where the header size is set.&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
